Object.Field: Configuration #3 - IKM Oracle Control Append - Load By Partition - Synchronous - Enabled Constraints - Maintain Indexes

This package uses the scenarios of the mapping called "Configuration #3 - IKM Oracle Control Append - Load By Partition - Flow Control" to perform a full load of the partitioned table.
The mapping performs the upload operation with the IKM Oracle Control Append. The upload operation is NOT performed with partition exchange. Instead, it uses the traditional insert statements in order to upload the source data into the target table (the partitioned table).
This package and mapping has been added into this demo as a comparison tool. You can use this package to compare the performance of uploading source data into a partitioned table with traditional knowledge modules such as IKM Oracle Control Append.
Data is loaded asynchronously, by partition. The table constrains of the partitioned table are enabled during the entire upload operation. Indexes are also maintained during the upload operation (they are not dropped or rebuilt during the upload operation). The logging of the target table (the partitioned table) is disabled and enabled before and after the upload operation, respectively.
